A 43 year old man who tried to evade arrest by assaulting police
was arrested. This was at a joint operation between the Provincial
Extortion Task Team and Moorreesburg SAPS where suspect was arrested for
several charges. Police spokesman Captain Frederick Van Wyk said in a
statement, “On Thursday, 09 June 2022, members acted on information received of
a former SAPS member who was impersonating a police officer in Roosenhof, Malmesbury. “They raided the suspect’s place of residence and found
several police uniform items. The 43-year-old male tried evading arrest by
assaulting a police officer. “He was arrested for the possession of State property,
assault of a police officer, impersonating a police officer and resisting
arrest. Once charged, the suspect will appear in the Malmesbury Magistrate’s
court.” READ: ‘Cable thieves’ shoot, injure guards! In an unrelated incident, a suspect wanted in Hillcrest was
arrested by Citrusdal police last night.  A warrant of arrest was issued
in Gauteng, following a house robbery and murder in Hillcrest. Information
emerged revealing that the suspect resides in the Riverview informal settlement
in Citrusdal. Having confirmed the whereabouts of the suspect, an operation was
conducted and the suspect was arrested and detained. He will make his court
appearance in the Clanwilliam Magistrate’s court today. Van Wyk said in Nyanga police arrested four suspects who
robbed an off duty SAPS member in Browns Farm yesterday, 09 June 2022. The
Rondebosch based SAPS member was stopped by four suspects who pulled him out of
his car and assaulted him. The suspects fled with his wallet and firearm. The
members who were patrolling in the area spotted the four suspects and arrested
all four of them. The property was recovered including the firearm. The
suspects will appear in the Athlone Magistrate’s court, once charged.